               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-133-person1217">
                  EDWARD 
                  THOMAS
               <interp inst="t18190915-133-person1217" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-133-person1217" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-133-person1217" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am churchwarden of St. Olave, Silver-street. The prisoner had received relief as a <rs id="t18190915-133-deflabel709" type="occupation">pauper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190915-133-defend1216 t18190915-133-deflabel709"></join> from our parish. On Monday, the 16th of August, in the evening, he came to me, and said he had been to Woolwich, and obtained employment as a rigger at the dock-yard, at 1 l. a week, and requested I would advance him 10 s. or 12 s., that he might not draw upon his employers before Saturday night - I gave him 10 s. on the parish account. He called again on Thursday evening, and was apprehended on the Saturday following.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-133-person1218">
                  THOMAS 
                  TAYLOR
               <interp inst="t18190915-133-person1218" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-133-person1218" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-133-person1218" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am foreman of the riggers at Woolwich. The prisoner was not employed there. We give the riggers 16 s. 6 d. a week.</p>
